==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: irritating
<hw>irritating</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>causing
annoyance.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> annoying, galling, chafing, nettlesome, pesky,
pestiferous, pestilent, plaguy, plaguey, teasing, vexatious,
vexing.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>causing irritation of living tissue; -- used of
physical stimuli.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> irritant, irritative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>causing pain or physical discomfort; <as>as, an
<ex>irritating</ex> burr under his stocking</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> painful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irritation</ent>⟦br⟧
